10:
Alk, my friend...
"Trick" is too strong of a word.
14:
Oh really?! I wasn't aware that your
definition of "someplace nice" included
the jaws of death!
17:
Oh, the real show's further in. Think of
this little ditty as the opening act.
21:
Are you going to do something about
them or not?
25:
You know I'm not about that violence.
I'm counting on you, buddy-o.
29:
That's it! I don't want to hear any more
of your lies!
33: Lies? Oh no. I really am counting on you.
41:
Look at you, twirling on that stage.
You could be a ballerina.
And now for the grand finale!
55:
We're here, Alk. This is what I was
meaning to show you.
60:
Hold up. My life's still flashing before
my eyes.
68:
Nexus. This is the place where androids 
come together and form new life.
69:
The process itself is a tad dull though.
This machine scans the parents' data
and sort of balls it together into a new
entity.
72:
So this is where droids are born, huh?
It's beautiful.
76: Yes, quite an spectacular design, isn't it?
78: By the by, human data is also fair game.
86:
Yes. And since the two of us are
already here... care to try it?
91:
And spend the next eighteen years
raising a kid with YOU? I'd rather eat
scrap metal.
95:
What if you cared for the little buster,
and I paid child support?
98:
Wow. Exhibit A of why Dia thinks you're
trash.
103:
You sure know how to hit a fellow where
it hurts. But, all right. I'm sorry.
107:
All joking aside, I've been wanting to
show you this place for a while.
121:
Oh, nothing. What say we start heading
home?
128:
Yes, and cleared the path for others.
That's all I wanted to do. Give the
people back their future.
130:
Though, let's just say, I also snuck
a tasty treat for myself.
140: I hope this isn't another one of his plots.
142:
I hate to let you down, old boy,
but "I" am always plotting.
145:
Still, to tell the truth, if "I" weren't,
I wouldn't be here.
150:
That's right, chums. But not the Regis
you know.
153:
That one's made up of my old memories
that were wiped by the Administrator.
157:
Huh? Then why didn't they just go back
inside your head?
160:
Because that would've been against our
wishes. It was far tidier to craft
a separate Regis.
164: So THAT'S why you went to Nexus!
167:
And I must say, Alk, you did a swell job
beating a path to the place. You have
my warmest thanks.
168:
If you hadn't, why, I'd be stuck sharing
a body with THIS miserable lout!
172:
Yeah, that would've been bad...
Glad I was able to help!
176:
I say, why are you treating that Regis
so much better than this Regis?
178:
Hah. Haven't "I" ever heard the saying,
"As you make your bed, so you must lie
upon it?"
186:
No need to fret. I'll be taking my leave
now. Must be a dreadful nightmare
having TWO Regises in one space.
188:
Oh, and l'autre moi... I'll be assuming
full responsibility for the past. So turn
over a new leaf. Start living in the
present, eh?
197:
Can we exchange you for the other
Regis?
203:
Oh, mon amie... Why do you reserve
your coldest winds for me?
